      • apply

        public ExportAddressTable apply(MemoryMappedPE mmBytes,
                                long rva,
                                int entries,
                                long virtualAddress,
                                long fileOffset)
        Creates an instanceo of the export address table by loading the addresses from the given export section bytes.

        Parameters:
        mmBytes - the bytes of the export section
        rva - the relative virtual address for the export address table (found in the data directory table)
        entries - number of entries in the export address table
        virtualAddress - the virtual address the rva is relative to
        fileOffset - the file offset where the EAT starts
        Returns:
        an instance for the export address table
